Johannesburg – South African seasoned chef, Dorah Sithole has died. Apart from being a chef, Sithole was a writer, former editor of True Love, food stylist, recipe developer, a trained Cordon Bleu chef and an author. At this stage, further details about Sithole’s death remains unclear. The country’s official Twitter account confirmed her passing on Monday afternoon. It is believed that the 67-year-old died on Sunday at a Johannesburg hospital. Tributes poured in on social media for the South African food icon. View the tributes below:        Follow @SundayWorldZA on Twitter and @sundayworldza on Instagram, or like our Facebook Page, Sunday World, by clicking here for the latest breaking news in South Africa. To Subscribe to Sunday World, click here. Sunday World 